e Loyalty’ websites, software, or other services.</li></ul><p>In the event of a business consolidation, merger, acquisition, asset purchase or sale of or by Blue Pure Loyalty, we may transfer your Personal Information on the condition that the acquiring or surviving entity adheres to terms no less protective than this Privacy Policy for the purpose of safeguarding your Personal Information.</p><p><strong>SECURITY</strong></p><p>The security of your Personal Information is important to us. When you enter sensitive information, we encrypt that information using secure socket layer technology (SSL).</p><p>We follow generally accepted industry standards to protect the personal information submitted to us, both during transmission and once we receive it. No method of online transmission or electronic storage is 100% secure, however. Therefore, while we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.</p><p>If you are visiting Blue Pure Loyalty from a location outside of the U.S., your information will be conveyed through U.S. servers and your personal information will be subject to jurisdiction in the U.S. All information you provide to us will be processed and securely maintained in web servers and internal systems located within the U.S.</p><p>If you have any questions about security on our web site, you can email us at info@bluepure <a href="http://loyalty.com">loyalty.com</a>.</p><p><strong>INTERNATIONAL TRANSFERS</strong></p><p>Blue Pure Loyalty stores Personal Information in the cloud, our servers, and the servers of our service providers. To facilitate our global operations, we may transfer and access such information from around the world, including to servers located in the United States. By providing information to Blue Pure Loyalty, you consent to the transfer and storage of Personal Information in these locations.</p><p><strong>REQUESTING YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION.</strong></p><p>You 